commit.message:
Fix computing bytes fields (memory and disk space)

It seems that all new RouterOS versions are reporting those fields
as bytes, so remove the multipliers introduced in 460236c.

Successfully tested on the following RouterOS versions:
- 6.38.5 (stable)
- 6.42.1 (stable)
- 6.42.3 (stable)
- 6.43rc42 (testing)

The revert is partial (not affecting CPU frequency).
Closes #6
src/main.c: Fix accidental assignment in if-condition.

Added connect timeout

Minor cosmetic fixes by @manio

src/routeros_api.h: Document the members of ros_connect_opts_t.

In particular, document the unit (seconds) of the timeout parameters.
cosmetics and typos

Added configurable receive timeout

Refactored by @manio (including @octo comments)
Merge branch 'remove-gcrypt'

Replace MD5 with internal implementation and remove gcrypt dependency

This also fixes random collectd crashes on startup because the gcrypt was not
initialized properly (so putting into syslog):
collectd: Libgcrypt warning: missing initialization - please fix the application

This problem is also solved with the above transition.

Add source files for internal MD5 implementation

http://openwall.info/wiki/people/solar/software/public-domain-source-code/md5
Update ChangeLog and finally tag a new release
read_exact: cover EINTR errno

read_exact: Fix endless loop after device disconnect

read_exact() function doesn't take into account return value of 0
from read() call. This generally means EOF and it was happening
eg. when remote device was rebooted.

The code was hanging in endless loop in the block:
  while (have_bytes < buffer_size) {...}

This was resulting in 100% CPU usage of collectd routeros plugin
process.

This commit is fixing this. After this, collectd is able to detect
connection problems and is reconnecting.

Sample collectd log output when mikrotik has been restarted:
Jul 10 14:47:58 collectd[31733]: routeros plugin: ros_interface failed: Protocol error
Jul 10 14:47:58 collectd[31733]: read-function of plugin `routeros/10.2.0.9' failed. Will suspend it for 20.000 seconds.
Jul 10 14:48:19 collectd[31733]: routeros plugin: ros_connect failed: No route to host
Jul 10 14:48:19 collectd[31733]: read-function of plugin `routeros/10.2.0.9' failed. Will suspend it for 40.000 seconds.
<successfull reconnect and gathering data continues...>

ros_parse: fix uptime parsing

It seems that recent RouterOS versions are reporting uptime in the format:
1w4d1h16m55s
... while the _sstrtodate() function was expecting the following formatting:
6w6d18:33:07

This commit is fixing it by talking into account the new formatting
(the old one should also work).

Closes #9

commit.message: Bump version to 1.1.3 and update ChangeLog (unreleased).
interface: Parse counters as 64bit value
librouteros(3): Added documentation for "system health"
Added the "system-health" high-level command

Add support for RouterOS 6.x splitted counters in interface

The newer RouterOS doesn't use the counters in format:
  Param 9: bytes = 1090924066,2872515632
but it is now splitted, like:
  Param 13: rx-byte = 9003084616
  Param 14: tx-byte = 37225808829

The change affected only the interface list (/interface/print), but not the
counters in registration table (/interface/wireless/registration-table/print).

This commit is trying to detect this and convert it accordingly.

Problem is also reported here:
http://forum.mikrotik.com/viewtopic.php?t=65227

commit.message:
src/ros.c: Use the "host" variable.

Otherwise some compilers complain about an unused variable. Also it is
much nicer to read.

src/ros.c: Check the return value of fgets().

Some compilers are unhappy when this return value is ignored.
Bump version to 1.1.2 and update ChangeLog.

ros_connect, create_socket: Free (struct addrinfo *).

It was only freed in case of an error.
